Southampton lost 2-1 to Stoke at the Britannia on Saturday . 
  Morgan Schneiderlin opened the scoring but Mame Diouf equalised for the home side . 
  Saints missed the chance to close the gap on Manchester City to two points . 
  Charlie Adam scored the winner for Stoke with six minutes remaining . 
  Ronald Koeman says Saints will not give up on Champions League . 
 